    <p>Hello! Welcome to BotHub.Studio's developer documentation!</p>
    <p>BotHub.Studio is a backend platform for bot deployment and management. Our goal is to help developers to focus on their own logic not on engineering issues.</p>

    <h2 id="why">Why BotHub Studio?</h2>

    <br/>

    <h3 id="why-code">Take Code Ownership</h3>

    <p>There are many services already on chatbot service ecosystem.</p>
    <p>Some of them are great, especially for UI chatbot builder even non-developer can build a chatbot with ease.</p>
    <p>But we are developers. We don't want to melted down our efforts into someone's service UI which can't save it to my local machine or to GitHub. Moreover, sometimes we want to use other tools which a service doesn't provide yet.</p>
    <p>We don't have enough time and money to make whole part of chatbot by our own hands. So we are searching some tools or frameworks. But we want to own most important part at least.</p>
    <p>BotHub.Studio helps us to deploy and run my own code. They only supports backend service. I can own important core of my bot and control it.</p>

    <h3 id="why-backend">Backend Free</h3>

    <p>There are many 'Make a chatbot in 10 minutes' stuffs today. (Even BotHub.Studio says that!)</p>
    <p>But, getting more traction, you need to solve many hard engineering problems.</p>

    <ol>
      <li>You should handle increasing throughput</li>
      <li>Send massive messages to messenger platform efficiently to keep reasonable responsiveness</li>
      <li>Sometimes message orders messed up</li>
      <li>Someday you need a scheduler</li>
      <li>Someday you need a database. Moreover each users need their own persistent storage</li>
      <li>You need a deployment automation to eliminate SPOF to improve a reliability</li>
      <li>Someday you need a logging system</li>
      <li>... And statistics, and analytics base on that</li>
    </ol>

    <p>You need a skilled backend software engineer to solve these tough issues. Hiring this kind of engineer is not so easy, but it costs high even you get in touched them.</p>
    <p>Imagine this, many backend software engineers all over the world solves same issues in their own company. How inefficient it is. You can use your energy to solve better, more important, more productive issues.</p>
    <p>Bothub.Studio is operated by senior backend engineers, we improve a backend of bothub.studio by every day. We only charges only a dozens of dollar per month. It's much like a supporting open source project. You pay $10 per month, we can build a more robust backend, everyone can enjoy the platform.</p>

